  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Plato the Younger,Epigrammatist, 1st cent... This author, whose creative 
    period was probably around the middle of the 1st cent. AD, is regarded by the Anthologia Palatina as responsible for 
    three epigrams, each consisting of one distich: a variation on the theme of the blind man and the lame man (Anth. Pal. 9,13), and two descriptions of works of art (9,748
    751). Three other epideictic epigrams of the same kind, marked 'P.', have also been correctly attributed to him (9,747
    16,161 248, the last two purely monostichic)..."Albiani, Maria Grazia (Bologna) "Plato." Brill’s New Pauly. Brill Online, 2013. Reference. Tufts University Library. 07 June 2013.</mads:note>
